## Summary of All Changes

| File | What changed | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `wii_audio.h` | `GBA_FRAMES` changed from 549 → 548 | Both modes must use identical buffer size to prevent SPU reallocation and `ready=false` reset |
| `spu.h` | Removed `bufferIn/Out/Size` heap pointers; added `buffers[2][548]` inline double-buffer; changed `getSamples()` signature to `bool getSamples(uint32_t*, int)` | Eliminates null-pointer read, heap alloc per callback, and ownership confusion |
| `spu.cpp` | Rewrote `getSamples()` and `pushSample()`; removed `~Spu` deallocation | Fixes invalid reads; swap is now atomic under `PPCIrqLock`; no heap traffic |
| `main.cpp` | Removed `PullSpuSamples()`; added `s_spuStaging[]`; simplified `AudioThreadMain` | No `delete[]`, no intermediate heap buffer, single call path for both NDS and GBA |


===
The change is purely in `getSamples()` and `pushSample()`. Here is the updated logic for all three modes:

- **fpsLimiter == 2**: strict sync (busy-wait), previously what mode 1 did — block until data is ready / consumed
- **fpsLimiter == 1**: play whatever is in the buffer right now, never block
- **fpsLimiter == 0**: silent unless buffer is full (unchanged)

```cpp
bool Spu::getSamples(uint32_t *dst, int count) {
    if (count > SPU_BUF_FRAMES)
        count = SPU_BUF_FRAMES;

    bool wait = false;

    if (Settings::fpsLimiter == 2) {
        // Strict: block this thread until the emulator has a full buffer ready.
        PPCIrqState st = PPCIrqLockByMsr();
        bool isReady   = ready;
        PPCIrqUnlockByMsr(st);

        if (!isReady)
            KThrQueueBlock(&waitQueue2, 1);
        // After unblocking, ready is guaranteed true by pushSample.
    }
    else if (Settings::fpsLimiter == 1) {
        // Relaxed: serve whatever is in the completed buffer right now.
        // Never block — if nothing is ready we repeat the last sample.
        PPCIrqState st = PPCIrqLockByMsr();
        if (!ready) wait = true;
        PPCIrqUnlockByMsr(st);
    }
    else {
        // No limiter: silent unless a full buffer is ready.
        PPCIrqState st = PPCIrqLockByMsr();
        if (!ready) wait = true;
        PPCIrqUnlockByMsr(st);
    }

    if (wait) {
        PPCIrqState st   = PPCIrqLockByMsr();
        int         ri   = writeIdx ^ 1;
        uint32_t    last = buffers[ri][SPU_BUF_FRAMES - 1];
        PPCIrqUnlockByMsr(st);

        for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
            dst[i] = last;

        return false;
    }

    {
        PPCIrqState st = PPCIrqLockByMsr();
        int ri = writeIdx ^ 1;
        memcpy(dst, buffers[ri], (size_t)count * sizeof(uint32_t));
        ready = false;
        PPCIrqUnlockByMsr(st);
    }

    // Only wake the emulator back-pressure block in strict mode.
    if (Settings::fpsLimiter == 2)
        KThrQueueUnblockAllByValue(&waitQueue1, 1);

    return true;
}

void Spu::pushSample(int16_t sampleLeft, int16_t sampleRight) {
    buffers[writeIdx][bufferPointer++] =
        ((uint32_t)(uint16_t)sampleRight << 16) |
        ((uint32_t)(uint16_t)sampleLeft  & 0xFFFF);

    if (bufferPointer < SPU_BUF_FRAMES)
        return;

    if (Settings::fpsLimiter == 2) {
        // Strict: block until the audio thread has consumed the previous buffer.
        PPCIrqState st = PPCIrqLockByMsr();
        bool isReady   = ready;
        PPCIrqUnlockByMsr(st);

        if (isReady)
            KThrQueueBlock(&waitQueue1, 1);
    }
    // Modes 1 and 0: never block the emulator — just overwrite.

    {
        PPCIrqState st = PPCIrqLockByMsr();
        writeIdx ^= 1;
        ready     = true;
        PPCIrqUnlockByMsr(st);
    }

    bufferPointer = 0;

    // Only wake the audio thread in strict mode.
    if (Settings::fpsLimiter == 2)
        KThrQueueUnblockAllByValue(&waitQueue2, 1);
}
```

The key differences from before:

| Mode | `getSamples` | `pushSample` |
|------|-------------|--------------|
| 2 | blocks until emulator is ready | blocks until audio has consumed previous buffer |
| 1 | serves last buffer immediately, never blocks | overwrites freely, never blocks |
| 0 | serves silence if not ready, never blocks | overwrites freely, never blocks |

Mode 1 and 0 now share the same `pushSample` path which means the emulator thread is never stalled by audio in either of those modes. The only difference between them is that mode 1 will repeat the last completed frame when the emulator is ahead, while mode 0 serves silence in the same situation.
